It's a sign.

It's been battered by nothing but the rain and
blown by nothing but the wind. The letters are
hard to make out.
It's a barrel.\n< Serena >

Perhaps a passing carriage dropped it. It seems to
be empty inside.\n< Serena >
It's a stump.\n< Serena >

With monsters swarming like this, gathering
firewood is going to be quite a struggle.\n< Serena >

We must reduce the monsters' strength before
winter comes, or the town will freeze over if
people can't enter the forest.\n< Serena >
It's truly a matter of life and death.\n< Serena >
Firewood.\n< Serena >

We mustn't carelessly touch firewood in places
like this. It might be the town's property after
all.\n< Serena >
拾い部屋　ファンMOD
AudioManager.playBgm({"name":"Theme2","volume":100,"pitch":100,"pan":0})
Ah... are you doing okay?\n< Cecilia >
...it seems so. That's good.\n< Cecilia >

Um... you're Serena, right? You seem... smaller
somehow...\n< Cecilia >
Ah, Cecilia-sama. You're safe.\n< Serena >

Indeed... a lot has happened. Now, I am what you'd
call splendid.\n< Serena >
A lot has happened...?\n< Cecilia >
Ah! Serena!\n< Rena >
Hmm...? Rena-sama... is that you?\n< Serena >

It's a relief to see you unharmed. I'm glad
you're... alive.\n< Serena >

I saw a familiar figure amidst the sea of black
slimes. I thought it was Serena and went to
rescue...\n< Cecilia >
But it turned out to be someone else.\n< Cecilia >
So, who is this? Your daughter?\n< Cecilia >
...It might be so, or... it might not be.\n< Serena >
Huh? What? Are you kidding?\n< Cecilia >
Hmm~ Well, it's fine.\n< Cecilia >
So, what do we do now?\n< Cecilia >
There is something I must do.\n< Serena >
...I can hear a voice. From the town of Castellum.\n< Serena >
The voice of someone dear who saved me.\n< Serena >
A voice...? I don't understand, but...\n< Cecilia >

Well, you don't seem like a normal human right now
anyway.\n< Cecilia >

Don't tell me you're thinking of going to that
town filled with black slimes and monsters?\n< Cecilia >
...\n< Serena >
Cecilia-sama. May I ask for your cooperation?\n< Serena >
I have feelings that I must convey.\n< Serena >
...sigh.\n< Cecilia >

Just so you know, if it gets too dangerous, I'm
running away. And make sure to pay me properly for
this.\n< Cecilia >
I'll give you a discount for the friend's rate.\n< Cecilia >
Ah!\n< Serena >
I am grateful for your generous heart!\n< Serena >

Oh, right. If you're talking about gratitude, you
should also thank someone named Erika later on.\n< Cecilia >

Right after Castellum turned into that mess, she
was about to dive in looking for you in that
state.\n< Cecilia >

It was too reckless, so I stopped her, but in
exchange, she asked me to look for you.\n< Cecilia >
You have good friends, Serena.\n< Cecilia >
Erika-sama...\n< Serena >

By the way, she loaded me up with weapons for that
purpose...\n< Cecilia >

Well, it would be a waste to let these grenades?
go unused, and they might not work if they get
damp, so maybe I'll set off some big fireworks
before that happens.\n< Cecilia >

But even so, there are too many monsters in the
city. We'll use the underground waterways.\n< Cecilia >

I'll probably just be in the way. I'll be praying
for your safety.\n< Rena >
...\n< Rena >
Serena!\n< Rena >
It's because you were there, I came to see you!\n< Rena >
So...\n< Rena >
Thank you!\n< ??? >
And please, come back alive!\n< ??? >
I want to see you again!\n< ??? >
Don't say this is the end!\n< ??? >
I'll be waiting forever to see you again!!\n< ??? >
Ah!\n< Serena >

That's right. As long as I do not stop walking,
there will be a day when we meet again.\n< Serena >
Now, let us go forth. Lady Cecilia!\n< Serena >
